# dogfood-self-monitoring-precedence.ttl -- Composability declaration
# (v26.7.18). A single additive triple, NOT a standalone hook pack: it adds
# one `kh:after` triple to dogfood-lifecycle-pack's already-declared
# dfl:derive_review_obligation hook node (../hook.ttl), naming
# self-monitoring-pack's hook.ttl `smon:derive_escalation_obligation` as a
# same-load ordering dependency.
#
# WHY THIS IS A SEPARATE FILE, NOT A property on ../hook.ttl's own hook node
# directly: `hooks::compile_hooks` in praxis-graphlaw resolves every
# `kh:after` IRI at hook-pack-load time and returns a hard error
# ("unknown after-dependency") if the named hook is not present in THAT SAME
# load. Putting this triple directly on ../hook.ttl's hook node would make
# dogfood-lifecycle-pack's OWN derivation (Derivation power / Obligation
# lifecycle) fail to load standalone -- exactly the kind of unwanted
# cross-pack coupling a knowledge-hook pack must not impose on its primary
# consumer. This file's ONE triple is therefore additive: load it ONLY when
# composing dogfood-lifecycle-pack with self-monitoring-pack together, by
# concatenating ../hook.ttl + this file + self-monitoring-pack/hook.ttl into
# one `load_hook_pack` call (see the scratch-consumer test
# `cross_pack_precedence_resolves_and_both_packs_derive_over_one_union_graph`
# cited in README.md's "Composability — verified" section for the exact
# recipe and its real, passing result).
#
# This is the literal L5 composability bar: "Hook families form a
# governance stack; ordering and precedence are declared in RDF" -- the
# declaration lives here, in RDF, not in prose; `hooks::schedule_hooks`'s
# Kahn's-algorithm topological sort is what actually reads and enforces it.
#
# DISCLOSED VOLATILITY (found live, this session): self-monitoring-pack's
# own hook.ttl is a SEPARATE pack's file this change does not edit, and its
# hook IRIs are not stable across that pack's own maintenance passes -- this
# session found its hook set had already been restructured (from a single
# `smon:derive_escalation_obligation` hook, cited in this pack's own
# ontology.ttl comments and README.md draft text, to four parameterized
# hooks: `smon:prioritize_escalation_obligation_{low,medium,high}` and
# `smon:flag_ungoverned_transition`) partway through this same session,
# most likely by a concurrent agent working that pack in parallel. The
# `kh:after` triple below names `smon:flag_ungoverned_transition` (the
# current hook this session verified exists), NOT the originally-planned
# `smon:derive_escalation_obligation` (which no longer exists in that file
# as of this pass). If self-monitoring-pack renames or removes
# `flag_ungoverned_transition` in a LATER pass, this file's `kh:after` will
# again fail to resolve with "unknown after-dependency" the next time both
# packs are co-loaded -- this is a real, disclosed cross-pack coupling risk
# inherent to declaring precedence against another pack's hook IRI by name,
# not a defect unique to this file.

@prefix kh:   <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/praxis/kh#> .
@prefix dfl:  <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/dogfood-lifecycle#> .
@prefix smon: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/self-monitoring#> .

dfl:derive_review_obligation kh:after smon:flag_ungoverned_transition .
